\subsection{Model Architectures}
\label{sec:models}

\subsubsection{YOLOv8}
YOLOv8 \cite{yolov8} is the eighth generation of the Ultralytics
YOLO family and adopts a fully \textit{anchor-free} detection
paradigm. The backbone is a modified CSPDarknet that employs C2f
(cross-stage partial with two bottlenecks) modules for improved
gradient flow. A PANet (Path Aggregation Network) neck fuses
multi-scale feature maps from three backbone stages, enabling
detection across a range of object scales. The detection head is
\textit{decoupled}: separate branches predict
objectness/classification and bounding-box regression, allowing
each branch to specialise independently. The model was pretrained
on the COCO dataset \cite{coco} and fine-tuned on the custom gear
dataset at $640\times640$ input resolution using the Ultralytics
Python library \cite{yolov8}.

