\subsection{Training Configuration}
\label{sec:training}

All models were trained on Google Colab with GPU acceleration
(NVIDIA Tesla T4). The key hyperparameters are summarised below.

\textbf{YOLOv8 and YOLOv11:}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Framework: Ultralytics Python library (PyTorch backend
        \cite{pytorch})
  \item Epochs: 100; Batch size: 16
  \item Optimizer: SGD with momentum 0.937 and weight decay
        $5\times10^{-4}$
  \item Learning rate: 0.01 with cosine annealing decay
  \item Loss: Binary Cross-Entropy (classification) +
        Complete IoU/CIoU (regression)
  \item Checkpoint saving: every 5 epochs to Google Drive
        (required to recover from Colab session disconnections)
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Faster R-CNN:}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Framework: PyTorch Torchvision detection module
        \cite{pytorch}
  \item Epochs: 100; Batch size: 16
  \item Optimizer: AdamW with learning rate $1\times10^{-3}$,
        cosine decay
  \item Loss: Cross-Entropy (classification) +
        Smooth~$L_1$ (box regression)
  \item Checkpoint saving: every 5 epochs to Google Drive
        (training required several hours per run; Colab
        disconnections would otherwise lose all progress)
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Evaluation Metrics}
\label{sec:metrics}

The following standard detection metrics were used for evaluation.
Let TP, FP, and FN denote true positives, false positives, and
false negatives, respectively.

\begin{equation}
  \text{Precision} = \frac{\text{TP}}{\text{TP} + \text{FP}}
  \label{eq:precision}
\end{equation}

\begin{equation}
  \text{Recall} = \frac{\text{TP}}{\text{TP} + \text{FN}}
  \label{eq:recall}
\end{equation}

\begin{equation}
  F_1 = 2 \times \frac{\text{Precision} \times \text{Recall}}
               {\text{Precision} + \text{Recall}}
  \label{eq:f1}
\end{equation}

\begin{equation}
  \text{mAP} = \frac{1}{N}\sum_{i=1}^{N} \text{AP}_i
  \label{eq:map}
\end{equation}

where $N$ is the number of classes and $\text{AP}_i$ is the area
under the Precision-Recall curve for class $i$ at an IoU threshold
of 0.50. Additional deployment metrics---inference time per image
(ms), frames per second (FPS), and model file size (MB)---were also
recorded to characterise real-time applicability.

\subsection{Web Application: CASTVISION}
\label{sec:webapp}

The CASTVISION web application provides a graphical front-end for
the inspection system. Users can either {upload images} from
disk or {use a connected camera} to capture all four views
directly through the browser interface. The interface presents:
\begin{itemize}
  \item Four image panels labelled VIEW~1 through VIEW~4, one per
        camera capture.
  \item A {RUN FULL INSPECTION} button that triggers
        inference across all four views simultaneously.
  \item A real-time {System Log} showing detection events
        per view.
  \item A {Final Verdict} panel displaying {``OK''}
        (all four views defect-free, shown in green) or
        {``REJECTED''} (defect detected in one or more
        views, shown in red), together with a per-view result
        breakdown indicating which specific views failed.
\end{itemize}

